24/04/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The OSCE reaffirmed its strong support Friday (21 April) for the development of a National Referral Mechanism in Macedonia, as part of the efforts to provide adequate identification and protection of trafficking victims. 
Experts from the Macedonian government and the OSCE met in Skopje to discuss the results of a related project, funded by the OSCE and implemented by the ministry of labour and social policy. 
During the talks, OSCE agreed to donate equipment to eight regional centres for social work in Macedonia. 
(OSCE Web site - 21/04/06)
